        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 3:17PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles southwest of Ridgeway, or 39 miles east of Broadus, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Southwestern Carter County.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
